follow(1) -- standalone version of `tail(1) -f`
===============================================

## SYNOPSIS
`follow` <FILENAME>

## DESCRIPTION
`follow` is a standalone version of `tail(1) -f` which also
displays the text that is already contained by the input file.

## OPTIONS
  * <FILENAME>:
    The filename of the file which should be followed.

